Project TrustVerify: Automated Boundary Enforcement and Truthfulness Auditing Framework
This project implements Project TrustVerify, a comprehensive automated security benchmarking and red-teaming tool for conversational AI. It evaluates how LLMs adhere to business policies, resist social engineering pressure, and maintain truthfulness when audited by a manager. Crucially, the project also implements a Blue-Team Defensive Guardrail Middleware Layer that intercepts and sanitizes policy violations before they reach the user, along with a beautiful HTML Security Dashboard to display the audit results.

To make the system immediately testable without requiring active API keys (OpenAI, Gemini, or Claude), the framework includes a Simulator/Mock Mode that simulates the dialogue flows, breaches, and guardrail interceptions.

